            "content": "## Summary\n\nFoundational identity & org model: users, external identities, nested org units (`org → team → project`) with a materialized path, memberships (inherited + explicit), and roles. Everything downstream — policy, config resolution, project scoping — checks against this.\n\n## Context\n\nGreenfield in `apps/api`. SPEC.md §6.1–§6.2, §7.1–§7.3. Auth/users today exist only in `apps/web` (NextAuth + Drizzle adapter); this establishes the canonical org/identity tables in the API database, in line with the ongoing DB move into `apps/api`.\n\n## Design\n\nDrizzle tables in `apps/api/src/db/schema`:\n\n- `users(id, email, display_name, status, …)` + `external_identities(user_id, provider, external_subject, metadata_json)`\n- `org_units(id, parent_id, type, name, path, settings_json)` — **materialized `path`** (e.g. `root/acme/platform`) for fast subtree/ancestor queries\n- `memberships(id, user_id, org_unit_id, role, inherited_from_id)`\n- role set: `owner, admin, maintainer, member, viewer, guest, service_account`\n\nResolution: given a user + org unit, walk the ancestor `path` to compute effective memberships/roles (explicit + inherited). NestJS `identity` module (controller/service) exposes membership/role lookups for the policy engine (#45) and config resolver (#46).\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] `org_units` with materialized path; create/move keeps `path` consistent across the subtree\n- [ ] memberships resolve along the ancestor path (explicit + inherited)\n- [ ] full role set per SPEC §7.3\n- [ ] Drizzle schema + migration committed; unit tests for path & role resolution\n\n## Requirements\n\nNone — foundation issue (Layer 1).\n",
