            "content": "## Summary\n\nResolve effective configuration across the scope chain (`global → org path → project → user → chat → run`) and persist an immutable **snapshot per run**, so every run is reproducible and auditable.\n\n## Context\n\nSPEC.md §6.3–§6.4. Depends on the org model (#44) for the scope chain and the policy engine (#45) for deny-based capability removal. This answers \"why was this tool/model available for this run?\".\n\n## Design\n\n- `configs(id, scope_type, scope_id, config_json, version)` — one row per scope that sets values.\n- Explicit **merge strategy per setting** (SPEC §6.3): `providers: override_by_id`, `mcp_servers / skills / rag_sources: additive_with_deny`, `commands: additive_with_override`, `model_policy / network_policy: most_restrictive`.\n- `ConfigResolver.resolve(context) -> EffectiveConfig`, then strip any capability denied by policy (#45).\n- `run_config_snapshots(run_id, snapshot_json, computed_at, config_version_ids, policy_version_ids)` written when a run starts (consumed by #48).\n- \"Explain effective config\" endpoint returning the resolved value **plus provenance** (which scope set each setting).\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] documented merge strategy applied per setting class\n- [ ] immutable snapshot persisted on run start\n- [ ] explain endpoint shows the source scope + version per setting\n\n## Requirements\n\n- #44 — org model (scope chain)\n- #45 — policy engine (deny-based capability removal)\n",
