            "content": "## Summary\n\nStream run events to the client by cursor; on page refresh, **replay from the last seen sequence** so in-flight progress is never lost.\n\n## Context\n\nSPEC.md §9.4. Depends on the run-event store (#48). This delivers the \"every long-running operation is resumable\" principle on the web surface.\n\n## Design\n\n- `GET /api/v1/runs/{id}/events?after_sequence=N` (SSE), reading ordered rows from `run_events`.\n- Client subscribes by cursor; on mount/reload it fetches the latest run state, replays events after the last sequence it saw, then continues live.\n- Reconnect with backoff; a completed run streams the remaining event tail and then closes.\n- Fits the existing `apps/web` App Router API conventions (`app/(chat)/api/v1/*`).\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] SSE endpoint streams ordered events filtered by `after_sequence`\n- [ ] reloading mid-run restores progress purely from persisted events (no loss)\n- [ ] dropped connections resume from the last sequence\n\n## Requirements\n\n- #48 — durable run pipeline (run-event store)\n",
