            "content": "## v0.1: Minimal Q&A harness\n\nThe smallest useful version: single-user, single-model **streaming** Q&A — no worker, no queue, no tools, no supervisor. Built per agents-best-practices (\"smallest reliable single-loop harness\"). Durable runs (v0.2) and governance (v0.3) come later.\n\n### Architecture overview\n\nA user message is answered by **one streaming model call**. A typed session/event model (#53) feeds a cache-aware context builder; a thin `ModelClient` (#54) calls one provider with the user's key; the loop (#55) streams and persists. Budgets + cost/cache telemetry (#56) wrap it, compaction (#57) keeps long chats in-window, and a minimal eval set (#58) gates release. The existing `langgraph-supervisor` chat path is replaced by this single-model loop.\n\n### Key design decisions\n\n- One streaming model call, **not** a supervisor graph (multi-agent deferred until evals justify it).\n- No worker/queue — stream directly from the API (the durable-run pipeline is the v0.2 upgrade).\n- Stable, cache-aware prompt prefix from turn one (cache hit rate is the cost floor).\n- One provider, user-supplied key, behind a `ModelClient` interface (full BYOK is v0.4).\n- Answer-only (Level 0/1) autonomy; tools/permissions arrive with later milestones.\n\n### Layer 1: Foundation\n\n- [ ] #53 — chat session/event model + cache-aware context builder\n- [ ] #54 — minimal model integration (one provider, user key)\n\n### Layer 2: Loop\n\n- [ ] #55 — single-model streaming Q&A loop (replace supervisor) (requires #53, #54)\n\n### Layer 3: Hardening & release gate\n\n- [ ] #56 — per-run budgets + cost/token/cache telemetry (requires #55)\n- [ ] #57 — conversation context compaction (requires #53, #55)\n- [ ] #58 — minimal Q&A eval set (requires #55)\n\n### Dependency graph\n\n```mermaid\nflowchart TD\n    C53[\"#53 session + context builder\"]\n    M54[\"#54 model integration\"]\n    L55[\"#55 streaming loop\"]\n    B56[\"#56 budgets + telemetry\"]\n    K57[