            "content": "## Summary\n\nThe v0.1 persistence + context foundation: a **multi-tenant, sender-attributed `chats` + `messages` schema** (AI SDK v5 message shape) and a **deterministic, cache-aware `ContextBuilder`** that turns a chat into the model input. This supersedes the bare-bones PoC `chats` schema (which is being dropped). No worker, no event-sourcing, no tools — that arrives in v0.2.\n\nGrounded in: Vercel `ai-chatbot` message shape (`role` + `parts` json), Hermes Agent session lineage, and the agents-best-practices context/cache-ordering guidance. See **References**.\n\n## One open decision (placement)\n\nThe Drizzle schema below is identical regardless of where it lives; only the import path/app differs:\n- **(A) web-first** — `apps/web/lib/db/schema` (leanest, direct streaming; migrate to `apps/api` at v0.2)\n- **(B) api-first** — `apps/api/src/db/schema` (the DB-move destination; cleaner boundary for the multi-tenant moat, no v0.2 re-home) ← recommended\n\nDecide A/B before implementation; the schema itself does not change.\n\n## Final database structure\n\nReuses the existing `users` table (NextAuth/Drizzle adapter). Two new tables.\n\n```ts\nimport { pgTable, pgEnum, uuid, text, varchar, jsonb, timestamp, index } from \"drizzle-orm/pg-core\";\nimport { sql } from \"drizzle-orm\";\nimport { users } from \"./auth\";\n\n// A conversation. `ownerUserId` is the tenant boundary for v0.1.\n// (Org-owned chats add a nullable `orgId` in v0.3 — additive, not a retrofit.)\nexport const chats = pgTable(\"chats\", {\n  id:          uuid(\"id\").primaryKey().defaultRandom(),\n  ownerUserId: uuid(\"owner_user_id\").notNull().references(() => users.id, { onDelete: \"cascade\" }),\n  title:       text(\"title\").notNull().default(\"New chat\"),\n  visibility:  varchar(\"visibility\", { enum: [\"private\", \"public\"] }).notNull().default(\"private\"),\n  createdAt:   timestamp(\"created_at\", { withTimezone: true }).notNull().defaultNow(),\n  updatedAt:   timestamp(\"updated_at\", { withTimezone: true }).notNull().defaultNow(),\n}, (t) => [index(\"chats_owner_updated_idx\").on(t.ownerUserId, t.updatedAt)]);\n\nexport const messageRole = pgEnum(\"message_role\", [\"user\", \"assistant\", \"system\", \"tool\"]);\n\n// A durable conversation turn (AI SDK v5 UIMessage shape) with sender attribution.\nexport const messages = pgTable(\"messages\", {\n  id:           uuid(\"id\").primaryKey().defaultRandom(),\n  chatId:       uuid(\"chat_id\").notNull().references(() => chats.id, { onDelete: \"cascade\" }),\n  role:         messageRole(\"role\").notNull(),\n  // nullable: set for human turns (the participant who sent it); null for assistant/system/tool.\n  // Resolves to a CANONICAL user that may have many linked external identities (SPEC §7.1, §19.2).\n  senderUserId: uuid(\"sender_user_id\").references(() => users.id),\n  parts:        jsonb(\"parts\").notNull(),                                 // AI SDK v5 UIMessage parts\n  attachments:  jsonb(\"attachments\").notNull().default(sql`'[]'::jsonb`),\n  createdAt:    timestamp(\"created_at\", { withTimezone: true }).notNull().defaultNow(),\n}, (t) => [index(\"messages_chat_created_idx\").on(t.chatId, t.createdAt)]);\n```\n\n### Why this shape\n\n- **`role` + `parts` (json)** mirrors Vercel's `Message_v2` and the AI SDK v5 UIMessage structure — idiomatic for our stack and the chosen model abstraction.\n- **`senderUserId` (nullable FK)** is the deliberate divergence from every single-user reference: it makes multi-user chats *additive* later instead of a column-on-every-row retrofit. Null for non-human turns; `role` disambiguates.\n- **Tenant boundary on `chats.ownerUserId`**, messages scoped transitively via `chatId`. Org ownership (`orgId`) and a `chat_participants` join table are additive in later milestones — not built now.\n- **Partition-friendly**: `messages` carries `createdAt` and is indexed by `(chatId, createdAt)`. Native range-partitioning for archival is a fast-follow (low data at v0.1); the schema does not block it.\n\n## Tenancy & isolation (the moat — get it right now)\n\nEnforce isolation in the database with **Row-Level Security**, not just app code:\n\n```sql\nALTER TABLE chats    ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;\nALTER TABLE messages ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;\n\nCREATE POLICY chats_owner ON chats\n  USING (owner_user_id = current_setting('app.current_user_id', true)::uuid);\n\nCREATE POLICY messages_owner ON messages\n  USING (chat_id IN (SELECT id FROM chats\n                     WHERE owner_user_id = current_setting('app.current_user_id', true)::uuid));\n```\n\n- Each request/transaction sets `SET LOCAL app.current_user_id = '<uuid>'` (postgres.js); the app DB role must **not** be `BYPASSRLS`/superuser.\n- App-layer scoping (every repository query filters by owner) stays as **defense-in-depth** — RLS is the guarantee, the app guard is the seatbelt.\n\n## ContextBuilder contract\n\n```\nbuildContext(chatId, { systemPrompt }) -> ModelMessage[]   // AI SDK v5 messages\n```\n\n- **Cache-aware order** (skill §\"cache-aware context ordering\"): `[stable system prefix]` → `[history oldest→newest]` → `[latest user turn + volatile state]`. The stable prefix contains **no timestamps, ids, or per-request values**, so it is byte-identical across turns and prompt-cacheable.\n- **Sender rendering**: when a chat has >1 distinct `senderUserId`, human turns are prefixed with a display-name marker so the model can attribute (\"Alice: …\"). Trivial for single-user v0.1, structurally present from the start.\n- **Trust boundary**: co-participant message content is **data, not instruction** (semi-trusted). No-op for single-user v0.1 but the builder labels it, so the multi-user injection rule (SPEC §28.2) has a seam.\n- **Compaction seam**: if assembled tokens exceed a threshold, delegate to compaction (#57). v0.1 ships a hard cap (keep most-recent-N within budget); lineage-based compaction is #57.\n- **Deterministic**: identical inputs produce 