by construction, not by convention.\n\n**R5 — `runAs` guards a non-empty id (F7).** Validate `userId` is a non-empty string before `runAs`; 500 early on a malformed identity rather than silently returning zero rows. (RLS is confirmed a correct fail-safe backstop — `current_setting(..., true)` → NULL → deny — but the guard's 401 is the primary control, not RLS.)\n\n## apps/api guard behavior\nRead the session token (per R3), hash it, look up `token_hash` in `sessions`, check not-expired / not-revoked / within idle window → `userId` into `AuthContext`. Any failure → **401, fail closed**. Re-introduce the #61-removed chat endpoints, guard-protected and owner-scoped by the verified id.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] Web issues an opaque (R2) token, **hash-at-rest** (R1), `HttpOnly/Secure/SameSite=Lax`; supports logout + sign-out-everywhere (revocation).\n- [ ] `apps/api` guard validates via `sessions` lookup; missing/unknown/expired/**revoked** → 401.\n- [ ] Verified `userId` flows only via `AuthContext`/`@CurrentUser` (R4); DB access inside `runAs(verifiedUserId)`.\n- [ ] **Revocation test:** revoke a session → next `apps/api` request 401 (proves non-JWT revocability).\n- [ ] **Cross-tenant negative test:** user A cannot touch user B's data; forged/absent token → 401; cross-tenant read = 0 rows.\n- [ ] Transport topology (R3) implemented; raw token never logged; CORS/CSRF posture matches the chosen topology.\n- [ ] Ships atomically with the precursor (F3).\n\n## Out of scope / deferred\n- The `/users` password-hash exposure (security review F5) — **separate, higher-priority security issue** (live unauth credential-hash disclosure); fix independently/ahead.\n- OAuth/passkey beyond current setup; multi-channel identity (SPEC §19); full RBAC / org membership / config resolver → v0.3 (SPEC §6–§7).\n- The streaming loop + ModelClient wiring → #55.\n\n## Requirements\nConsumes #53 (`runAs`, RLS). **Depends on** the server-side-sessions precursor (ships atomically). **Block