            "content": "## Summary\n\nStand up **pg-boss on the existing Postgres** as the run queue + scheduler — no Redis, no separate scheduler service (Postgres-first, SPEC §24.0).\n\n## Context\n\nSPEC.md §9.6, §24.0. Foundation for the durable run pipeline (#48). pg-boss needs no Postgres extension and lives in its own schema alongside the Drizzle tables.\n\n## Design\n\n- Add `pg-boss` to `apps/api`; start a singleton in the worker process and a thin publisher in the API process.\n- Queues: `runs` with priority lanes; scheduled jobs via pg-boss cron.\n- Wrap behind a `Queue` interface (`enqueue`, `consume`, `schedule`, `cancel`) so it can later swap to Redis+BullMQ or Temporal (SPEC §23.4) **without touching callers**.\n- Configure per-user / per-project concurrency limits, retries with exponential backoff, and archiving.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] enqueue/consume with retries + backoff and dead-letter handling\n- [ ] a scheduled (cron) job demonstrated\n- [ ] `Queue` interface in place; pg-boss is the only wired implementation\n- [ ] no Redis; runs on the same Postgres instance\n\n## Requirements\n\nNone — foundation issue (Layer 1).\n",
