ted` → fail-closed input validation, which the auth surface needs regardless). `@nestjs/swagger` derives **`openapi.json`** from those DTOs + explicit response types (e.g. `PublicUser`, never ad-hoc objects), emitted as a build artifact. No hand-written spec; **client/SDK codegen is deferred** (post-v0.1, once the surface is stable / a non-TS consumer exists) — the spec is the durable asset, the generated client is disposable.\n\n## Acceptance\n- [ ] `/auth/v1` login + sessions-as-resource implemented; sessions hashed-at-rest, opaque.\n- [ ] Guard validates per request; missing/unknown/expired/**revoked** → 401.\n- [ ] **Revocation test:** revoke → next request 401. **Cross-tenant test:** A can't touch B's data; cross-tenant read = 0 rows.\n- [ ] Re-introduced chat endpoints live under `/api/v1`, guard-protected + owner-scoped by the verified id.\n- [ ] Input validated via DTO + `ValidationPipe` (unknown/invalid field → **400**); `openapi.json` is emitted on build and covers `/auth/v1` + the `/api/v1` chat routes (SSE stream endpoint excepted — documented, not codegen-modeled).\n\n## Out of scope\nOAuth/passkey providers (later); full RBAC / org membership → v0.3; the apps/web thin-client refactor → #63; the streaming loop → #55. **Client/mobile SDK codegen** off the spec → deferred until a stable surface + real second consumer.\n\nConsumes #53. **Blocks #55 and #63.**\n",
