            "content": "## Summary\n\nImplements **#60** — authentication in `apps/api`. `apps/api` becomes the auth authority with two independently-versioned surfaces (SPEC §22.0):\n\n- **`/auth/v1`** — `register`, `login`, `me`, and sessions-as-resource (`GET /sessions`, `GET|DELETE /sessions/current`, `DELETE /sessions/:id`, `DELETE /sessions` with `?scope=all`).\n- **`/api/v1`** — domain routes (chats), guard-protected and owner-scoped.\n\nAuth rests on **revocable server-side sessions**: an opaque `crypto.randomBytes(32)` token, **SHA-256 hashed at rest** (raw token never stored), validated per request by `SessionAuthGuard` (Bearer → cookie). The verified `userId` flows only through a request-scoped `AuthContext` (`@CurrentUser`) into `TenantDbService.runAs(userId)`, so Postgres RLS runs under a trusted tenant — identity is **never** read from client input. Code-first OpenAPI throughout (class-validator DTOs + global `ValidationPipe` + `@nestjs/swagger` → `openapi.json`).\n\nThis replaces the NextAuth-JWT direction (JWT can't be revoked); `apps/web` still runs its legacy auth and is cut over separately in #63.\n\n## Commits\n- `feat(api): add auth v1 sessions` — the surface, guard, schema migration (`0006`), DTOs/responses, OpenAPI.\n- `fix(api): #60 code-review fixes + nodenext module resolution` — high-effort review follow-ups (below) + replacing the fragile bcrypt path-hack with a CommonJS-clean `bcryptjs` under `moduleResolution: nodenext`.\n- `test(api): commit auth e2e (real HTTP) + run it in the DB harness` — durable end-to-end verification.\n\n## Code-review fixes folded in\n- Removed the unauthenticated `/users` HTTP controller (an email-enumeration oracle + an unhashed-password create); `UsersService` stays for internal DI.\n- `ParseUUIDPipe` on `/auth/v1/sessions/:id` (a malformed id was an unhandled 500).\n- `409` (not 500) on the register email-uniqueness race.\n- Case-insensitive Bearer scheme (RFC 6750).\n- Session cookie `Secure` gated by env s