            "content": "# #55 — Single-model streaming Q&A loop (apps/api SSE)\n\nThe smallest reliable single-loop harness: a user message is answered by **one streaming model call**, persisted, with no worker, queue, tools, or supervisor. Lives in **`apps/api`** (it owns the DB; `apps/web` is a thin client). Replaces the `langgraph-supervisor` chat path in `apps/web`. Specced against agents-best-practices (MVP Builder Mode) and verified against `vercel/ai-chatbot` (our exact stack: Next.js + Drizzle + AI SDK v5).\n\nConsumes **#53** (`ContextBuilder`, `chats`/`messages` schema, `MessagesRepository`), **#54** (`ModelClient`/`streamText`, credential resolution), **#60** (`SessionAuthGuard` → verified `userId` → `TenantDbService.runAs` → RLS). **Blocks #56, #57, #58.**\n\n---\n\n## MVP boundary\n\n**In:** one authenticated user posts a message to a chat they own → the API persists it, builds a cache-aware context from stored history, makes **one** streaming model call with the user's key, streams the answer back over SSE, and persists the assistant message + token usage.\n\n**Out (deferred, tracked):** tools / multi-step loops; the durable worker + queue (#48/#50, v0.2); refresh-safe resumable stream replay (#49, v0.2); budgets + cost/cache aggregation & enforcement (#56); lineage-based compaction (#57); the eval set (#58); full BYOK credential vault (v0.4); multi-channel delivery (v0.9). Autonomy is **Level 0/1, answer-only** — the only side effect is persisting messages.\n\n**Assumption:** one provider (OpenAI-compatible) in v0.1, behind `ModelClient` (#54). The model id is a fixed default (`DEFAULT_OPENAI_MODEL`) or a simple per-request/per-chat selection; full model governance is v0.4.\n\n---\n\n## API surface (RESTful, per SPEC §22.0)\n\n```\nPOST /api/v1/chats/:id/messages        (guarded; :id is ParseUUIDPipe)\n  body:  { message: { parts: [{ type: \"text\", text: string }] } }   # the NEW user message only\n  resp:  200 text/event-stream          # AI SDK v5 UI-message-stream (SSE); the streamed assistant message\n         404  chat not found / not owned by caller\n         400  malformed id / invalid body (ValidationPipe)\n         402  no model credential for the user (MissingModelCredentialError) — fail BEFORE streaming\n         401  no/invalid session\n```\n\n- The client sends **only the new message** — history is loaded server-side from the DB (verified against ai-chatbot: it does the same; the client is never trusted with history). This keeps the server authoritative and RLS-scoped.\n- A `POST` that returns a stream is the idiomatic AI SDK pattern; the resource created is the assistant message, delivered incrementally. The user message is created as a side effect of the same call (it has no independent lifecycle in v0.1).\n- DTO: `CreateMessageDto` (class-validator) — `message.parts` non-empty, each text part non-blank, `@MaxLength` on text. Per the §22.0 DTO discipline.\n\n---\n\n## Core loop\n\nThe load-bearing rule: **no DB transaction is held open while the model streams.** DB work is two short `runAs` transactions — before and after the stream — with the model call in between holding nothing.\n\n```\n1. Guard → userId (verified). ParseUUIDPipe → chatId. ValidationPipe → message.\n2. runAs(userId)  [short tx #1, RLS engaged]:\n     a. findById(chatId, userId)  → 404 if absent/not owned\n     b. MessagesRepository.create({ chatId, role:\"user\", senderUserId:userId, parts })\n     c. history = findByChatId(chatId, userId)   # includes the just-saved user msg, ordered by seq\n   → buildContext(history, { systemPrompt })     # pure, cache-aware (ContextBuilder, #53)\n3. credential = resolveModelCredential(userId)    # #54; missing → 402 BEFORE any stream\n   client = ModelsService.createOpenAIClient(credential, model)\n4. result = client.streamText({\n     messages: context,\n     abortSignal: req.signal,                     # client disconnect → abort the model call\n     onFinish: async ({ text, usage, finishReason }) => {\n       runAs(userId) [short tx #2]:               # persist assistant + usage; NO tx held during stream\n         MessagesRepository.create({ chatId, role:\"assistant\", senderUserId:null,\n                                     parts:[{type:\"text\", text}], usage })\n     },\n   })\n5. return result.toUIMessageStreamResponse({ onError })   # SSE; onError → safe string, never a stack trace\n```\n\nStopping: a single call with **no `stopWhen`/`maxSteps`** (those only matter with tools). The turn ends when the model finishes or the client aborts.\n\n---\n\n## Harness boundary\n\n- **Model proposes** the answer text only (no actions — no tools in v0.1).\n- **Harness (apps/api) does** everything else: auth, ownership, persistence, context assembly, credential resolution, streaming transport, usage capture, error shaping. The model never touches the DB or the credential.\n\n## Instruction architecture\n\n- **System prompt** = a small static string, the **stable cacheable prefix** — `ContextBuilder` places it first and it contains **no per-request data** (no ids, timestamps, user values), so it is byte-identical across turns (prompt-cache floor). v0.1: a single hardcoded assistant system prompt (e.g. identity + answer-only behavior). Per-project/per-chat system prompts are a later milestone (§6–§7).\n- **History** = `ContextBuilder` output, oldest→newest, capped at `maxMessages` (hard cap; lineage compaction is #57). Sender-attribution prefix (already data-not-instruction) when >1 human sender.\n- No developer/user instruction layering beyond this in v0.1.\n\n## Tools\n\n**None.** Explicitly: no tool registry, no `tools`/`experimental_activeTools`, no `stopWhen`. (agents-best-practices: don't expose tools before a single-loop harness passes evals. ai-chatbot's 5 tools + approval flow are all \"extra\" we omit.)\n\n## Context & memory\n\n`ContextBuilder` (#53): `[system] → [history oldest→newest, capped]`, ordered by `seq` (deterministic — better than ai-chatbot's `createdAt` ordering, which ties for same-tx writes). No retrieval/RAG (v0.6). Compaction beyond the hard cap is #57.\n\n## Model layer & a required #54 extension\n\n`ModelClient` (#54) currently exposes `streamText({ messages, system, abortSignal })` and returns the AI SDK `StreamTextResult`. **#55 requires extending `ModelStreamInput` with `onFinish?: (e: { text: string; usage: LanguageModelUsage; finishReason: string }) => void | Promise<void>`** so the harness can capture the final text + token usage for persistence. (`createUIMessageStream`'s own `onFinish` yields `{ messages }` but **not** `usage` — usage lives on `streamText`'s `onFinish`/result. ai-chatbot never captures it; we do.) `onError` is handled at the loop via `toUIMessageStreamResponse({ onError })`, so it stays out of the client interface.\n\n**Credential source (v0.1 stopgap):** the user's key via `resolveModelCredential(userId, resolver)` (#54). v0.1 resolver may read a single configured key or a simple per-user store; the encrypted BYOK vault + per-scope resolution is v0.4. Missing credential → **402, before streaming**.\n\n## Safety\n\n- **Prompt-injection:** answer-only + **no tools** ⇒ minimal blast radius — injected instructions in chat content can at worst shape the text reply, not trigger an action. User/sender content is **data, not instruction** (ContextBuilder already treats it so). An injection probe is part of #58's eval set.\n- **Tenant isolation:** every DB touch is inside `runAs(userId)` → RLS; identity is the verified session id, never client input (#60). Cross-tenant write/read is impossible by construction.\n- **Secrets:** the model credential is resolved server-side, never logged, never sent to the client. The raw key never enters a response or the stream.\n- **Abort:** the request `AbortSignal` is wired into `streamText` so a client disconnect cancels the upstream model call (no orphaned generation / wasted spend).\n\n## Observability & cost (the #56 seam)\n\n- `onFini