ports, `useMe` stale-time override, per-chat state owner.\n- **Code review (`/code-review --fix`)** applied 4 fixes on top of the implementation:\n  - **Open-redirect** guard on the login `callbackUrl` (same-origin relative paths only).\n  - The global 401 cache-clear+redirect no longer fires for `/auth/v1/login|register` (a 401 there is bad credentials, not a revoked session — the form error now shows instead of reloading).\n  - Dropped a redundant awaited `invalidateQueries(me)` after login/register (avoids a Set-Cookie race; `useMe` refetches on mount anyway).\n  - Fixed a `transport.test.ts` type error that `next build` doesn't catch.\n- **Spec-conformance review:** all 10 hard requirements PASS, all non-goals respected, no gaps.\n\n## Verification\n- `pnpm --filter web lint` ✓ (pre-existing unused-import warnings only) · `pnpm --filter web typecheck` ✓ · `pnpm --filter web test` ✓ (3/3)\n- `pnpm --filter api lint|build|test` ✓ · `apps/api/scripts/rls-test.sh` ✓\n- `pnpm --filter web build`: green with network (fetches `next/font/google`); not runnable in the no-network review sandbox.\n\n## Notes / follow-ups (tracked, out of scope here)\n- Submitting a first message then immediately selecting another chat within the create round-trip can let the resolved `createChat` override the selection — narrow race; resolved by the optional client-supplied chat `id` upgrade.\n- Deferred: `GET /api/v1/models` + wiring model selection into the loop; `GET /api/v1/chats/:id/messages` + a `/chat/[id]` deep-link route for history rehydration; chat title generation on the API.\n\nCloses #63.\n",
